#: ../../G/gas.rst:5
msgid "gas"
msgstr "gas"

#: ../../G/gas.rst:7
msgid "[as in ‘gas chamber’]"
msgstr "[‘ガス室(gas chamber)’のように]"

#: ../../G/gas.rst:9
msgid ""
"interj. A term of disgust and hatred, implying that gas should be dispensed "
"in generous quantities, thereby exterminating the source of irritation. "
"\"Some loser just reloaded the system for no reason! Gas!\""
msgstr ""
"間投詞 "
"嫌悪と憎悪の言葉。ガスをふんだんに撒き、それによって苛立ちの元を絶滅させるべきだという含意がある。「どこかの間抜けが理由もなくシステムをリロードした!Gas!」"

#: ../../G/gas.rst:14
msgid ""
"interj. A suggestion that someone or something ought to be flushed out of "
"mercy. \"The system's getting :ref:`wedged` every few minutes. Gas!\""
msgstr "間投詞 誰かまたは何かを慈悲で流し去るべきだという提案。「システムが数分ごとに\\ :ref:`wedged`\\ になる。Gas!」"

#: ../../G/gas.rst:19
msgid ""
"vt\\. To :ref:`flush` (sense 1). \"You should gas that old crufty "
"software.\""
msgstr "他動詞 \\ :ref:`flush`\\ する(語義1)。「あの古びたソフトウェアはgasすべきだ。」"

#: ../../G/gas.rst:24
msgid ""
"[IBM] n. Dead space in nonsequentially organized files that was occupied by "
"data that has since been deleted; the compression operation that removes it "
"is called degassing (by analogy, perhaps, with the use of the same term in "
"vacuum technology)."
msgstr ""
"[IBM] 名詞 "
"非逐次的に構成されたファイル内の、すでに削除されたデータが占めていた空き領域。これを取り除く圧縮操作はdegassing(脱ガス)と呼ばれる(おそらく、真空技術における同じ用語の使い方との類推による)。"

#: ../../G/gas.rst:27
msgid ""
"[IBM] n. Empty space on a disk that has been clandestinely allocated against"
" future need."
msgstr "[IBM] 名詞 将来の必要に備えてこっそり割り当てられた、ディスク上の空き領域。"
